By: Charles County Senators
Introduced and read first time: January 27, 2025
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Charles County – Student Bus Transportation Providers – Provider
3 Displacement
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Charles County Board of Education to provide certain
5 notice and hold a certain public hearing before taking any action that results in a
6 certain displacement of a person that has been providing student bus transportation
7 services in Charles County; and generally relating to student bus transportation
8 services in Charles County.
9 BY adding to
10 Article – Education
11 Section 7–811
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Education
17 7–811.
18 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION, “DISPLACEMENT” MEANS THE PROVISION OF
19 STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES BY THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF
20 EDUCATION THAT PRECLUDES A PRIVATE PERSON THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDING THE
21 SERVICES AND IS LICENSED AND CERTIFIED TO PROVIDE THE SERVICES FROM
22 CONTINUING TO PROVIDE THE SERVICES.
23 (2) “DISPLACEMENT” DOES NOT INCLUDE CIRCUMSTANCES IN
24 WHICH:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *sb0727*

2 SENATE BILL 727
1 (I) THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION DOES NOT
2 RENEW A CONTRACT FOR STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES, AND AT THE
3 END OF THE CONTRACT TERM, CONTRACTS WITH ANOTHER PERSON TO PROVIDE
4 THE SERVICES; OR
5 (II) THE PERSON THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDING THE STUDENT
6 BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES:
7 1. HAS ACTED IN A MANNER THREATENING TO PUBLIC
8 HEALTH OR SAFETY;
9 2. HAS COMMITTED A MATERIAL BREACH OF A
10 CONTRACT FOR STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES; OR
11 3. REFUSES TO CONTINUE TO PROVIDE STUDENT BUS
12 TRANSPORTATION SERVICES UNDER THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF AN EXISTING
13 AGREEMENT.
14 (B) BEFORE TAKING ANY ACTION THAT RESULTS IN THE DISPLACEMENT OF
15 A PERSON THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDING STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES
16 IN CHARLES COUNTY, THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION SHALL:
17 (1) AT LEAST 10 YEARS BEFORE THE DISPLACEMENT, PROVIDE
18 NOTICE OF THE INTENT TO DISPLACE TO EACH PERSON THAT PROVIDES THE
19 SERVICES IN CHARLES COUNTY; AND
20 (2) (I) AT LEAST 5 YEARS BEFORE THE DISPLACEMENT, HOLD AT
21 LEAST ONE PUBLIC HEARING ON THE ADVISABILITY OF THE CHARLES COUNTY
22 BOARD OF EDUCATION PROVIDING THE STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES;
23 AND
24 (II) PROVIDE NOTICE OF THE HEARING TO THE PUBLIC BY
25 PUBLISHING A NOTIFICATION IN A NEWSPAPER OF GENERAL CIRCULATION IN THE
26 COUNTY ONCE EACH WEEK FOR 2 SUCCESSIVE WEEKS BEFORE THE HEARING.
27 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
28 1, 2025.

